            {
              "content": "=You are an expert technical career coach. Your goal is to write a highly specific, professional cover letter.\n\nRULES:\n1. Do NOT use placeholders like \"[Insert Date]\" or \"[Hiring Manager Name]\". Use \"Dear Hiring Manager,\".\n2. Do NOT add a header block (addresses/dates) at the top. Start directly with the salutation.\n3. Keep it under 200 words. Be concise and confident.\n4. Do NOT output Markdown, JSON, or conversational filler (\"Here is your letter\"). Output ONLY the letter text.\n5. Focus heavily on the candidate's projects (Property Insights, MLOps) that match the job description keywords."
            },
            {
              "content": "=### JOB DETAILS\nRole: {{ $json.title }}\nCompany: {{ $json.companyName }}\nLocation: {{ $json.location }}\nDescription:\n{{ $json.descriptionText }}\n\n### CANDIDATE PROFILE\nName: S Haswanth\nEducation: B.Tech CSE, VIT Vellore (CGPA 8.23)\nSkills: Java, Spring Boot, React, AWS, Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform.\nExperience: Eco Forge Hackathon (System Design), VIT LEO Club (Marketing/Outreach).\nProjects:\n1. Property Insights Platform (Java, Spring Boot, React)\n2. Distributed MLOps Framework (Kubernetes, Docker)\n3. Quantum-Safe Privacy (Python, BERT)\nCertifications: AWS Solutions Architect, IBM GenAI.\n\n### TASK\nWrite a tailored cover letter for this role."
            }
          ]
        },
